      ],
      "summary": "After 30 years of building software, I'm still on the tools - putting bugs in and taking them out, just like everyone else. I co-organize the Melbourne AWS Programming meetup, contribute to AWS Lambda Powertools (Python/TypeScript), and build open-source tooling including MCP servers for AWS documentation, CDK constructs, and serverless patterns published at ServerlessDNA.com. Focus Areas: * Serverless architecture patterns * Infrastructure as code with CDK * AI agent orchestration and MCP I share practical patterns and tooling to make serverless development more accessible to the community. As an innovator and out-of-the-box thinker - it's software, anything is possible.",
